  </script>
  <body>
    <div class="example" id="variables">
      <h2><a href="./">Lua by Example</a>: Variables</h2>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>In Lua, <em>variables</em> are declared on first use as global.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code empty leading">
            
          
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p><code>first</code> is a global variable.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="n">first</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&#34;initial&#34;</span>
<span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">first</span><span class="p">)</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>You can declare multiple variables at once.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="n">b</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">c</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span>
<span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">b</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="p">)</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Often variables should be declared local to avoid polluting the global scope.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="kd">local</span> <span class="n">d</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">true</span>
<span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">d</span><span class="p">)</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Variables have no predefined types; any variable may contain values of any type.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="kd">local</span> <span class="n">value</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&#34;starts as a string&#34;</span>
<span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="p">)</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Assigning a value of a another type</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="n">value</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">5</span>
<span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="p">)</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>To unset the value, assign nil</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code">
            
          <pre class="chroma">
<span class="n">value</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">nil</span>
<span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="p">)</span></pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            
          </td>
          <td class="code">
            
          <pre class="chroma"><span class="gp">$</span> lua variables.lua</pre>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      
